Definition: An alphanumeric identifier assigned to a specific patient.
Synonyms: patient id, Patient Identifier, patient_id, source id, source_id

Definition: The act of going to see some person or place or thing; it can cover a short or long period but refers to a non-permanent arrangement.
The assemblage of physical properties or qualities by which male is distinguished from female; the physical difference between male and female; the distinguishing peculiarity of male or female.
How long something has existed; elapsed time since birth.
Synonyms: AGE, Age, age, Aged, Chronological Age, Postnatal Age

Definition: The month in which a person was born.
The year in which a person was born.
The number of education years that a subject has competed.
Synonyms: EDUYRNUM, Number of Years of Education

Definition: A geographic ancestral origin category that is assigned to a population group based mainly on physical characteristics that are thought to be distinct and inherent.
A person having origins in any of the original peoples of Europe, the Middle East, or North Africa. (OMB)
Synonyms: Caucasians, Caucasian, Caucasoid, Occidental, White, white, WHITE, Whites

Definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of the Far East, Southeast Asia, or the Indian subcontinent, including for example, Cambodia, China, India, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Pakistan, the Philippine Islands, Thailand, and Vietnam. (OMB)
Synonyms: Asian Ancestry, ASIAN, asian, Asian, Asians

Definition: A person having origins in any of the Black racial groups of Africa. Terms such as "Haitian" or "Negro" can be used in addition to "Black or African American". (OMB)
Synonyms: BLACK OR AFRICAN AMERICAN, Black or African American, black or african american, BLACK_OR_AFRICAN_AMERICAN

Feature: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander
Definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, Guam, Samoa, or other Pacific Islands. (OMB)
Synonyms: native hawaiian or other pacific islander, NATIVE HAWAIIAN OR OTHER PACIFIC ISLANDER, Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander, NATIVE_HAWAIIAN_OR_OTHER_PACIFIC_ISLANDER

Definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of North and South America (including Central America) and who maintains tribal affiliation or community attachment. (OMB)
Synonyms: american indian or alaska native, AMERICAN INDIAN OR ALASKA NATIVE, American Indian or Alaska Native, AMERICAN_INDIAN_OR_ALASKA_NATIVE, First Nations, Native American, Native Americans

Definition: A social group characterized by a distinctive social and cultural tradition that is maintained from generation to generation. Members share a common history and origin and a sense of identification with the group. They have similar and distinctive features in their lifestyle habits and shared experiences. They often have a common genetic heritage which may be reflected in their experience of health and disease.
Synonyms: ETHNIC, Ethnic Group, Ethnic Origin, Ethnic Origins, ETHNICITY, Ethnicity, ethnicity

Definition: A demographic parameter indicating a person's current conjugal status.
Synonyms: MARISTAT, Marital or partnership status, Marital Status, MaritalStatus, MaritalStatusUB92

Definition: The preferred hand of use for controlled and efficient performance of motor tasks.
The vertical measurement or distance from the base to the top of an object; the vertical dimension of extension.
The vertical force exerted by a mass as a result of gravity.
An individual's weight in kilograms divided by the square of the height in meters.
Synonyms: BMI, Body Mass Index, body mass index, Quetelet Index, Vital Signs - BMI

Definition: The abdominal circumference at the navel.
The lateral prominence of the pelvis from the waist to the thigh.

The ratio of the abdominal circumference at the navel to maximum hip and buttocks circumference; looks at the proportion of fat stored on the body around the waist and hip. Carrying extra weight around the waist is a greater health risk than carrying extra weight around the hips or thighs.
Synonyms: Waist-Hip Ratio, Waist to Hip Ratio, WAISTHIP

Definition: A grouping of occupations and fields of study.
Used to describe an individual who does not experience sexual attraction.
A sexual attraction to members of both sexes, genders, or gender identities.
A sexual attraction to members of the same sex.
Sexual, romantic, or emotional attraction towards people regardless of their sex or gender identity, including agender, non-binary, and gender fluid.
A sexual attraction to members of the opposite sex.
